m from Antiquity to the Renaissance</a></i>, Cambridge: <a href="/wiki/Cambridge_University_Press" title="Cambridge University Press">Cambridge University Press</a>, 2013, pp. 381-382. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781107038233" title="Special:BookSources/9781107038233">9781107038233</a>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.iep.utm.edu/encyclop/">Encyclopedists</a>", <i>Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy</i>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Quintilian, <i>The Orator\'s Education</i>, 1.10.1: <i>ut efficiatur orbis ille doctrinae, quem Graeci</i> \xe1\xbc\x90\xce\xb3\xce\xba\xcf\x8d\xce\xba\xce\xbb\xce\xb9\xce\xbf\xce\xbd \xcf\x80\xce\xb1\xce\xb9\xce\xb4\xce\xb5\xce\xaf\xce\xb1\xce\xbd <i>vocant.</i></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">"Encyclopedia", <i>Oxford English Dictionary</i>, From the <i>The Book of the Governor</i> by Thomas Elyot (i. xiii): "The circle of doctrine is in one worde of greke <b>Encyclopedia</b>."</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-Konig-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Konig_8-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Konig_8-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Jason K\xc3\xb6nig and Gregg Wolf, (2013) "Introduction," <i><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=mfPXAAAAQBAJ&amp;dq=">Encyclopaedism from Antiquity to the Renaissance</a></i>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press, p. 1. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a> <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781107038233" title="Special:BookSources/9781107038233">9781107038233</a>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Pliny the Elder, <i>Natural History</i>, preface 14: <i>ante omnia attingenda quae graeci</i> \xcf\x84\xe1\xbf\x86\xcf\x82 \xe1\xbc\x90\xce\xb3\xce\xba\xcf\x85\xce\xba\xce\xbb\xce\xaf\xce\xbf\xcf\x85 \xcf\x80\xce\xb1\xce\xb9\xce\xb4\xce\xb5\xce\xaf\xce\xb1\xcf\x82 <i>vocant.</i> For the English translation, see <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus:text:1999.02.0137">here</a>. For the Latin/Greek original, see <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://data.perseus.org/citations/urn:cts:latinLit:phi0978.phi001.perseus-lat1:preface">here</a>.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">A <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.cmog.org/library/historia-naturalis">Venice incunabulum printed in 1469</a> has a blank space in the middle of second page where this phrase is supposed to be.</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Aventinus, Johannes, <i>Encyclopedia orbisqve doctrinarum&#160;: hoc est omniu[m] artiu[m]m, scientiaru[m], ipsius philosophiae index ac divisio scriptores earundem rerum&#160;...&#160;; ex Platone Aristotele</i>, Auguste&#160;: Miller, 1517. (WorldCat entry)</span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Ringelberg, Joachim Fortius, <i>Lucubrationes, vel potius absolutissima kyklopaideia</i>, 1541.<br />\nScalich, Paul, <i>Pauli Scalichii Encyclopaediae, sen Orbis disciplinarum epistemon</i> (<i>Paul Scalich\'s Encyclopaedia, or Knowle